---
/**
 * distributed-systems/fundamentals · Figure 3 — "clock skew eats data" (Level 3).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/distributed-systems/distributed-systems-fundamentals.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). References the shared #arwA arrowhead marker
 * rendered once by <Defs />. Lives as an .astro component because inline SVG with
 * kebab-case attrs is unreliable in MDX.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 560 150"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Two machine clocks drift apart; the later write carries the smaller timestamp and last-write-wins silently discards it"
    >
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="280"
                y="20"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">CLOCK SKEW silently eats data under last-write-wins</text
            >
            <rect x="20" y="40" width="150" height="40" rx="8" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></rect>
            <text x="95" y="58" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700"
                >Replica A clock</text
            >
            <text x="95" y="73" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#6b675f"
                >stamps write @ t=105</text
            >
            <rect x="390" y="40" width="150" height="40" rx="8" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></rect>
            <text x="465" y="58" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700"
                >Replica B clock</text
            >
            <text x="465" y="73" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#6b675f"
                >stamps LATER write @ t=103</text
            >
            <line
                x1="170"
                y1="60"
                x2="388"
                y2="60"
                stroke="#9a2417"
                stroke-dasharray="4 3"
                marker-end="url(#arwA)"></line>
            <text x="279" y="52" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#9a2417">~ms skew</text>
            <rect x="120" y="100" width="320" height="34" rx="8" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="280"
                y="121"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a2218">later write (103) &lt; earlier (105) → silently dropped</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Quartz drifts ~200 ppm (≈17 s/day); NTP narrows but can't share an instant and can step
        <em>backwards</em>. Wall-clock timestamps from different machines are not comparable for
        ordering. (DDIA Ch. 8, "Unreliable Clocks".)
    </figcaption>
</figure>
